-- Indian shares inch down; ITC slumps to lowest in about 10 months
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Mon Jun 23, 2014 06:11AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, June 23 (Reuters) - Indian shares edged down on Monday to close at their lowest in nearly 2-1/2 weeks as index heavyweight ITC <ITC.NS> slumped on tax hike worries.

ITC provisionally fell 5.4 percent, marking its biggest single day fall since September 2013, while Kotak Mahindra Bank <KTKM.NS> ended 4 percent down.